### addFullAddress() {#a1c9eea26c641feaf5808a6a18d4329fc}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const MachineInstrBuilder &amp; X86FastISel::addFullAddress (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstrbuilder">MachineInstrBuilder</a> &amp; MIB, <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/x86addressmode">X86AddressMode</a> &amp; AM)</>}>
Adds a complex addressing mode to the given machine instr builder.

Note, this will constrain the index register. If its not possible to constrain the given index register, then a new one will be created. The IndexReg field of the addressing mode will be updated to match in this case.
